				English Honours student with a background in programming, tech,
				research, finance and debates/public speaking. I started this
				blog to document my coding journey: documenting code, talk about
				my building process, lessons learnt and braincells lost.
				<br />
				<i
					>Maybe the real Google Summer of Code internship was the
					buggy code messes I built along the way.</i
				>
			</p>
			<div class="container-body">
				<b>My basic background:</b>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Currently pursuing an English Honours degree, Delhi
						University
					</li>
					<li>20 years old based out of New Delhi, India</li>
					<li>
						Interested in open source development, Content writing,
						Documentation Engineering
					</li>
					<li>Proficiency in Python and Javascript Development</li>
					<li>
						strong expertise in research, prompt engineering,
						English proficiency, writing documentation, business
						communication
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="container-body">
				<b>My projects:</b>
				<ul>
					<li>
						Debate Timekeeper project, built for the English
						Debating Society of my college
					</li>
					<li>This blog</li>
					<li>Debate Notetaking software - <a href="https://github.com/DefaltZ/debbynote">Debbynote</a></li>
					<li><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1PzVwI4iFyFOajz5slKnfvp53aP5tVSsHXOXdPV5uXcs/edit?usp=sharing">My Research/Writing portfolio</a></li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<p>
				<b
					>Find my complete resume linked <a
						href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/11MnkSXYOEhb1LapHWaml4ptGzzubEnAi/view?usp=sharing"
